<statement>
<p>Solve the equation: <m>\displaystyle{2}{\left({10}^{{-{8}{x}}}\right)}-{4}={0}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=</m><fillin characters="6" /> </p>
<p>Round to 3 decimal places.</p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>-0.038</li></ul></p><p><m>\displaystyle{2}{\left({10}^{{-{8}{x}}}\right)}-{4}={0}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{\left({10}^{{-{8}{x}}}\right)}=-{4}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{10}^{{-{8}{x}}}=-\frac{{4}}{{2}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{8}{x}={\log{{\left(-\frac{{4}}{{2}}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{\log{{\left(-\frac{{4}}{{2}}\right)}}}}{{-{{8}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}\approx-{0.038}</m></p>
</solution>
</myopenmath>

